        <div n="Z730050O" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-1"> 1</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="2" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-2">In Beauty or Witt&#13;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-3"> No Mortall as Yett</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-4"> To question the Empire has dar'd,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-5"> But men of discerning</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-6"> Have thought y<hi rend="sup">t</hi> in Learning,</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-7"> To Yeild to a Lady was hard.</l></lg><lg n="3" type="stanza"><l n="8" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-8">2</l></lg><lg n="4" type="stanza"><l n="9" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-9">Impertinent Schools,&#13;</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-10"> With musty dull Rules,</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-11"> Have Reading to Ladies deny'd,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-12"> So Papists refuse</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-13"> The Bible to use,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-14"> Least Flocks shoul'd be wise as their Guide.</l></lg><lg n="5" type="stanza"><l n="15" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-15">3</l></lg><lg n="6" type="stanza"><l n="16" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-16">'Twas a woman at first,&#13;</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-17"> (Indeed she was curs'd)</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-18"> In Knowledge y<hi rend="sup">t</hi> tasted delight;</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-19"> And Sages agree,</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-20"> The Law shou'd decree</l><l n="21" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-21"> To the first of Possessors y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Right</l></lg><lg n="7" type="stanza"><l n="22" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-22">4</l></lg><lg n="8" type="stanza"><l n="23" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-23">Then bravely Fair Dame&#13;</l><l n="24" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-24"> Renew the old Claim,</l><l n="25" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-25"> That to y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> whole sex does belong;</l><l n="26" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-26"> And let Men receive</l><l n="27" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-27"> From a second bright Eve,</l><l n="28" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-28"> The Knowledge of Right &amp; of Wrong.</l></lg><lg n="9" type="stanza"><l n="29" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-29">5</l></lg><lg n="10" type="stanza"><l n="30" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-30">But as the first Eve&#13;</l><l n="31" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-31"> Hard Doom did receive,</l><l n="32" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-32"> When only one Apple had she,</l><l n="33" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-33"> What a punishment now</l><l n="34" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-34"> Must be found out for You,</l><l n="35" xml:id="spp-Z730050O-line-35"> Who have tasted, &amp; robb'd, y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> whole Tree.Z730050O   </l></lg></div>
